Platform: MacBook Pro

Model Identifier: MacBookPro11,5
Processor Name: Intel Core i7, Haswell
Processor Speed: 2.5 GHz
Number of Processors: 1
Total Number of Cores: 4
L2 Cache (per Core): 256 KB
L3 Cache: 6 MB
Memory: 16 GB

Tensorflow installed from git master
Tensorflow version: head
Bazel version: bazel release 0.13.1-homebrew
CUDA/cuDNN version: N/A
GPU model and memory: N/A
Exact command to reproduce:

We use keras version 2.1.2

The model : https://github.com/svalleco/3Dgan/blob/master/keras/EcalEnergyGan.py
The test training script: https://github.com/svalleco/3Dgan/blob/master/keras/EcalEnergyTrain.py
Training dataset: https://cernbox.cern.ch/index.php/s/XIKU7gZA7jjzKsf

You’ll need to change the input file path in line 96
https://github.com/svalleco/3Dgan/blob/master/keras/EcalEnergyTrain.py#L96

The scripts uses a small subset of data and runs for only two epochs to speedup profiling.
The keras config file attached sets the data format and the backend (TF). It goes in the .keras directory.
